    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is generally best to favor high-quality, whole meat sources as the primary protein for an aging Labrador. While a mix might be acceptable if the plant-based ingredients are minimal and high-quality, sticking to meat-based proteins is preferred for optimal nutrient density. These pure sources often provide better amino acid profiles crucial for older dogs' health. Think of it this way: the meat should be the main ingredient, not just one of several options.",
      "source": "target",
